{{Infobox award | name = Global Jurist of the Year Award | image = Global Jurist Award.jpg | description = Judicial contributions to human rights and international criminal law | presenter = Center for International Human Rights, Bluhm Legal Clinic at Northwestern University School of Law | location = [[Chicago, Illinois]] | year = 2013 }} The '''Global Jurist of the Year Award''' or the '''Global Jurist Award''' is a recognition awarded annually by the Center for International Human Rights, an organization housed at the [[Bluhm Legal Clinic]] of [[Northwestern University School of Law]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Five Black Scholars Win Prestigious Awards|url=http://www.jbhe.com/2013/11/five-black-scholars-win-prestigious-awards/}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Global Jurist of the Year|url=http://www.law.northwestern.edu/legalclinic/humanrights/events/globaljurist/}}</ref> The award recognizes a sitting judge in recognition of that judge’s contribution to the advancement of international human rights law or international criminal law. Special account is taken of those who have shown outstanding dedication to the rule of law and courage in the face of adversity, including personal risk.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dikgang Moseneke to receive first annual Global Jurist of the Year Award|url=http://www.internationallawobserver.eu/2013/06/05/dikgang-moseneke-to-receive-first-annual-global-jurist-of-the-year-award/}}</ref> Jurists from all nations and tribunals are eligible for consideration and nominations are accepted from the public, usually between January and March of the award year, with the final selection of the recipient being made by the faculty of the Center. The prize is presented during a visit by the recipient to Northwestern Law School during fall semester of the award year.<ref>{{cite web|title=Northwestern Law to honor South African judge|url=http://www.northwestern.edu/newscenter/stories/2013/05/northwestern-law-to-honor-south-african-judge.html}}</ref> [[File:2013 